See the only thing verant will listen to is the LAW. Period.<br>
<br>
The LAW is represented by the BBB (Better Business Bureau).<br>
<br>
Yes, it is pathetic to have to go through these channels to accomplish anything, BUT can you convince yourself that Verant deserves to have their empathetic, understaffed, greedy mantra THRIVE without being checked into place ?<br>
<br>
There are currently over 100 BBB complaints about verant on record..and counting.  That translates into 100 ppl who had been wronged by Verants typocratic BS, and then ultimately compensated for it.  This is the ONLY channel that will have ANY effect.  Trust me I know..I am one of the 100.<br>
<br>
You see, it is like this.  Someone brought up a very good point about the people in Verant being a bunch of 20 year old kids, getting a ton of positive press release, and too much ego bosting feedback.  This derives the lack of professionalism that is our bane.<br>
<br>
Sony has a crack legal staff that does damage control for these people, and they ulitmately tell these punks what to do.<br>
<br>
The EULA that changed around christmas..you remember the change ?  Do you know what caused it to be changed ?  LOL, I am afraid I did.   See I held them accountable, and they didnt like it, so they tried to reword the EULA to accomodate their exposed arse.  Nice try, but they are still accountable IF HELD TO IT.<br>
<br>
Anyway...goto the BBB page for the San Diego area..this is where you can search for Verant, and be creative with your complaint.  You are doing Verant a disservice if you dont force them to clean house occcasionally..if not, the feeling of invulnerability will pervade the cubicle wonderland at Verants office, and the ego's within don't like to be told that they have to answer to anybody, and they'll kick and scream as the Legal counsel &quot;strongly suggests&quot; it is in their best interest to &quot;resolve the complaints&quot;..you get the picture ?<br>
